The paper deals with facial expression recognition using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of knowledge distillation (KD) for model compression suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on speed and efficiency may also suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
